---
description: SQL house conventions - apply when editing hand-written .sql files.
globs: "**/*.sql"
alwaysApply: false
---

When creating or editing hand-written SQL (`.sql`), follow the cross-engine conventions
carried by the `database-conventions` skill under `.cursor/skills/`: schema design,
migrations, indexes, and query safety. Prefer these over ad-hoc SQL.

If the `database-conventions` skill is not loaded, hold the line on the highest-value rules:
always qualify a `DELETE` / `UPDATE` with a `WHERE`, and make every migration forward-only
and idempotent rather than editing one already applied.

This is guidance, auto-attached by glob (not a hard block). Scoped to hand-written SQL; ORM
access written in `.cs` follows the C# conventions instead.
